sql:
SELECT users.user_name AS identity, comments.comment_text AS thoughts, comments.issue_id AS context
FROM comments
JOIN users ON comments.user_id = users.user_id;

external_knowledge:
- Seeds waiting to be sown: Issues that are currently open; 
- Type: Kind of issue (bug, feature, task); 
- Status: Current status (open in this context); 
- Field: The project the issue belongs to; 
- Gardeners: Project managers responsible for the project.
